result.execSummary:
The defendant Sharon L. Staten was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Identity Theft - Obtain Money or Credit [Modifiers: Conspiracy to Commit], a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.203(2)(a).
  • Fraudulent Claim/Income Tax Credit [Modifiers: Conspiracy to Commit], a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 71.83(2)(b)4.
  • Theft-False Representation >$10,000 [Modifiers: Party to a Crime], a class G felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.20(1)(d).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

The state makes corrections to its sentencing memorandum.
The defendant has stipulated to payment of restitution in the amount of $202, 520.00 to the Wisconsin Department of Revenue.

AS to count 1:    The Court sentenced the defendant to serve a term of IMPRISONMENT of 8 YEARS in the Wisconsin State Prisons, credit for 200 days time served.  CONFINEMENT of 4 YEARS  and EXTENDED SUPERVISION of 4 YEARS.

AS to count 2:    The Court sentenced the defendant to serve a term of IMPRISONMENT of 8 YEARS in the Wisconsin State Prisons, consecutive to count 1, credit for 0 days time served.  CONFINEMENT of 4 YEARS  and EXTENDED SUPERVISION of 4 YEARS.

AS to count 3:    The Court sentenced the defendant to serve a term of IMPRISONMENT of 4 YEARS in the Wisconsin State Prisons, consecutive to count 2, credit for 0 days time served.  CONFINEMENT of 2 YEARS  and EXTENDED SUPERVISION of 2 YEARS.
Sentences are to be served consecutive to each other and to any other sentence defendant may be serving.
The following conditions are as to counts 1,2,3:
-The Court ordered that all court costs, fines, surcharges and/or restitution be paid through collection by the Department of Corrections from 25% of prison funds under Sec. 973.05(4)(b) and as a condition of extended supervision.  Any amount remaining due and owing is subject to civil judgment. -Provide a DNA sample for the Data Bank and pay all appropriate costs.
-Seek and maintain employment.
